---
import ServiceLayout from '../../layouts/ServiceLayout.astro';

const title = 'Residential Floor Cleaning Dallas: Apartment & Condo Services | Commercial Cleaning Services of Dallas';
const description = 'Residential floor cleaning services in Dallas, TX. Apartment, condo, and multi-unit housing floor care and cleaning.';
const serviceName = 'Residential Floor Cleaning Services';
const targetKeyword = 'residential floor cleaning dallas';

const faqs = [
  {
    question: 'What types of residential properties do you clean?',
    answer: 'We clean apartment complexes, condominium communities, multifamily housing, senior living facilities, student housing, and apartment buildings. We provide common area cleaning, unit turnover cleaning, and ongoing floor maintenance services.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you clean individual apartments or just common areas?',
    answer: 'Both. We clean common areas including hallways, lobbies, and amenity spaces on a regular schedule. We also provide unit turnover cleaning for vacant apartments being prepared for new residents. Both services are available.'
  },
  {
    question: 'What is included in turnover cleaning?',
    answer: 'Turnover cleaning prepares vacant units for new residents. This includes thorough cleaning of all rooms, floor care, bathroom cleaning, kitchen cleaning including appliances, and addressing any issues from previous residents. Units are cleaned to move-in standards.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Can you clean different types of flooring?',
    answer: 'Yes. We clean carpet, hardwood, laminate, tile, vinyl, and other flooring materials common in residential properties. We use appropriate methods for each floor type including vacuuming, mopping, polishing, and deep cleaning.'
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you clean senior living and assisted living facilities?',
    answer: 'Yes. We clean senior living communities, assisted living facilities, and independent living communities. We understand the unique needs of these facilities including resident health considerations and working around resident schedules.'
  },
  {
    question: 'How do you handle cleaning around residents?',
    answer: 'For occupied units, we coordinate with residents and management. Common areas are cleaned on schedules that minimize resident disruption. Turnover cleaning happens in vacant units. Staff is trained to work respectfully in residential environments.'
  }
];

const relatedServices = [
  {
    slug: 'janitorial-services',
    title: 'Janitorial Services Dallas',
    description: 'Recurring commercial cleaning services.'
  },
  {
    slug: 'comprehensive-cleaning',
    title: 'Comprehensive Cleaning Dallas',
    description: 'Complete facility services and deep cleaning.'
  },
  {
    slug: 'project-based-cleaning',
    title: 'Project-Based Cleaning Dallas',
    description: 'One-time turnover and move-out cleaning.'
  }
];
---

<ServiceLayout
  title={title}
  description={description}
  serviceName={serviceName}
  targetKeyword={targetKeyword}
  faqs={faqs}
  relatedServices={relatedServices}
  parentPage="Services"
  heroImage="/images/Services/residential-floor-cleaning.webp"
>
  <p>
    Multi-unit residential properties in Dallas require cleaning that addresses both resident satisfaction and property management needs. <strong>Residential floor cleaning and facility services</strong> serve apartment complexes, condominium communities, senior living facilities, and multifamily housing. We maintain common areas, provide unit turnover cleaning, and care for floors throughout residential properties.
  </p>

  <p>
    Unlike commercial facilities, multi-unit residential properties serve residents who call these places home. Cleaning must happen without disrupting residents while maintaining high standards in common areas. Our services address lobbies, hallways, amenity spaces, and vacant units with approaches appropriate to residential environments.
  </p>

  <h2>Common Area Cleaning</h2>

  <p>
    Residential property common areas see daily resident traffic and require regular maintenance.
  </p>

  <h3>Lobby and Entrance Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Property entrances and lobbies create first impressions for residents and visitors. We clean entrance floors, dust furniture, clean glass doors and windows, empty trash, and maintain presentation. Mailroom areas and package rooms also receive regular cleaning.
  </p>

  <h3>Corridor and Hallway Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Apartment hallways see constant foot traffic from residents. We vacuum carpets or mop hard floors, clean walls and baseboards, remove spots, and address high-touch surfaces including elevator buttons and handrails. Hallway cleaning maintains property appearance and resident satisfaction.
  </p>

  <h3>Elevator and Stairwell Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Building elevators and stairwells require regular cleaning. We clean elevator interiors, buttons, and tracks. Stairwells are swept, and steps and landings are cleaned. Regular cleaning maintains these essential circulation areas.
  </p>

  <h2>Amenity Space Cleaning</h2>

  <p>
    Residential properties offer various amenities that require regular cleaning and maintenance.
  </p>

  <h3>Fitness Center Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Property fitness centers see regular resident use. We clean equipment, wipe surfaces, clean floors, and empty trash. We address sweat and residue while maintaining equipment. Fitness centers are cleaned to support resident use and hygiene.
  </p>

  <h3>Pool and Patio Area Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Pool areas, patios, and outdoor amenities require cleaning. We clean pool decks, furniture, and surrounding areas. We empty trash and address debris. Regular cleaning maintains these popular resident amenities.
  </p>

  <h3>Club Room and Community Room Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Community rooms, club rooms, and party spaces see use for resident events and gatherings. We clean these spaces thoroughly before and after events. Services include table and chair cleaning, floor care, kitchen cleaning, and trash removal.
  </p>

  <h3>Business Center Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Property business centers with computers, printers, and work areas require regular cleaning. We clean computer equipment, desks, surfaces, and floors. We address these spaces while being careful around electronic equipment.
  </p>

  <h2>Unit Turnover and Make-Ready Cleaning</h2>

  <p>
    Vacant units require thorough cleaning before new residents move in.
  </p>

  <h3>Apartment Turnover Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    When residents move out, units require thorough cleaning before new occupants arrive. We provide deep cleaning of all rooms including kitchen, bathrooms, bedrooms, and living areas. Units are cleaned to move-in standards.
  </p>

  <h3>Kitchen and Appliance Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Unit kitchens require detailed cleaning including appliances. We clean refrigerators inside and out, stoves and ovens, microwaves, cabinets, countertops, sinks, and floors. All surfaces are cleaned to remove residues from previous residents.
  </p>

  <h3>Bathroom Cleaning and Sanitization</h3>
  <p>
    Unit bathrooms receive thorough cleaning and sanitization. We clean tubs, showers, toilets, sinks, vanities, mirrors, and floors. Soap scum, mildew, and residues are addressed. Bathrooms are cleaned to sanitary standards.
  </p>

  <h3>Floor Care in Units</h3>
  <p>
    Unit floors are cleaned based on flooring type. Carpets are vacuumed thoroughly and receive deep cleaning as needed. Hard floors are swept, mopped, and polished. We address spots and stains to restore floor appearance.
  </p>

  <h2>Senior Living and Assisted Living Cleaning</h2>

  <p>
    Senior living facilities have specific cleaning requirements related to resident health and safety.
  </p>

  <h3>Common Area Cleaning in Senior Living</h3>
  <p>
    Senior living common areas including dining rooms, activity rooms, lounges, and corridors require regular cleaning. We clean these spaces thoroughly while being mindful of resident mobility and working around resident schedules.
  </p>

  <h3>Dining Room Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Senior living dining rooms serve residents daily. We clean dining tables, chairs, and serving areas. Floors are cleaned after meal service. We work around meal service times and maintain appropriate hygiene standards.
  </p>

  <h3>Resident Unit Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Assisted living and memory care units require cleaning around resident belongings. We clean floors, surfaces, and bathrooms while being careful not to disturb resident items. We coordinate with staff and respect resident privacy.
  </p>

  <h2>Laundry and Utility Room Cleaning</h2>

  <p>
    Residential property laundry and utility facilities serve residents and require regular maintenance.
  </p>

  <h3>Laundry Room Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Property laundry rooms see regular resident use. We clean folding tables, washers and dryer surfaces, sinks, and floors. We empty trash and clean lint traps. Regular cleaning maintains these functional spaces.
  </p>

  <h3>Trash and Compactor Area Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Trash rooms, compactor areas, and waste chutes require regular cleaning and sanitization. We clean these areas thoroughly to address odors and maintain hygiene. Floors and surfaces are washed and sanitized regularly.
  </p>

  <h2>Office and Administrative Area Cleaning</h2>

  <p>
    Residential properties include management offices and administrative spaces that require regular cleaning.
  </p>

  <h3>Leasing Office Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Property leasing and management offices require regular cleaning. We clean desks, surfaces, floors, and common areas. These spaces present professionally to prospective and current residents.
  </p>

  <h3>Maintenance Shop Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Property maintenance shops and storage areas require cleaning. We sweep floors, clean workbenches, and organize these spaces. Maintenance areas are cleaned to support efficient operations.
  </p>

  <h2>Specialized Residential Floor Care</h2>

  <p>
    Residential properties feature various flooring types that require specialized care.
  </p>

  <h3>Carpet Cleaning and Maintenance</h3>
  <p>
    Apartment and condominium carpets require regular vacuuming and periodic deep cleaning. We provide thorough vacuuming services and hot water extraction for deep cleaning. Carpet cleaning removes accumulated soil and extends carpet life.
  </p>

  <h3>Hardwood and Hard Floor Care</h3>
  <p>
    Hardwood, laminate, and other hard floors require regular maintenance. We sweep, mop, and polish floors as appropriate. Periodic deep cleaning and refinishing restores floor appearance and protects flooring investment.
  </p>

  <h3>Tile and Grout Cleaning</h3>
  <p>
    Tile floors in entries, kitchens, and bathrooms require regular cleaning. We mop and clean tile floors and address grout lines. Periodic deep cleaning removes accumulated soil from grout and restores tile appearance.
  </p>

  <h2>Dallas Residential Property Cleaning Coverage</h2>

  <p>
    Our residential property cleaning services cover Dallas and Dallas County. We clean multi-unit residential properties in Dallas, Highland Park, University Park, Farmers Branch, Irving, Garland, Richardson, Mesquite, Carrollton, and Addison.
  </p>

  <p>
    Contact us to discuss residential property cleaning for your Dallas apartment community or multifamily property. We will assess your needs and develop a cleaning program that serves your residents and property.
  </p>
</ServiceLayout>
